<title>USA: Gleason Q4 shr down after tax benefits.</title>
<headline>Gleason Q4 shr down after tax benefits.</headline>
<dateline>ROCHESTER, N.Y. 1997-02-03</dateline>
<text>
<p>1996			1995</p>
<p> Shr		 $1.24		    $3.83</p>
<p> Net		 6,557		    20,499</p>
<p> Sales	     69,955		   69,991</p>
<p> Avg shrs	  5,274		    5,345</p>
<p>		  YEAR</p>
<p> Shr		 $3.68		    $5.82</p>
<p> Net		 19,660		   30,827</p>
<p> Sales	     248,089		  197,046</p>
<p> Avg shrs	  5,341		    5,300</p>
<p>(All data above 000s except per share numbers)</p>
<p>NOTE: Q4 and full 1995 net income were increased by positive adjustments related to the recognition of deferred tax assets associated with charges recorded in prior years. Net income for 1995 using normalized tax rates would have been about $5.8 million, or $1.08 per share, for the fourth quarter and $13.3 million, or $2.51 per share, for the year.</p>
</text>
